== Translating plugin.xml
	
		(((i22n,plugin.xml)))
	

	
		Similar to the usage of keys in the application model, you can use the key prefixed with % in the
		_plugin.xml_
		file. The Eclipse tooling supports extracting existing
		`String`
		values from the
		_plugin.xml_
		file. Select your
		_plugin.xml_
		file, right-click on it and select
		menu:
			<guimenu>Plug-in Tools[Externalize Strings]
		.
	

	
image::pdetools10.png" scale="60" />
			
			<textobject>
				<phrase>Eclipse PDE Wizard for externizing plugin.xml</phrase>
			</textobject>
		
	
	
		Via
		menu:
			<guimenu>PDE Tools[Internationalize]
		you can also directly create
		one or several fragments for the result of
		the internationalization.
	


